    {
      "kind": "content",
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "discussion",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Discussion",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "This method can be invoked to synchronize hardware surface flushes with the window’s flushes. The window immediately disables screen updates using the "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/appkit/1473676-nsdisablescreenupdates"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " function and reenables screen updates when the window flushes. Sending this message multiple times during a window update cycle has no effect."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "To ensure that screen updates are reenabled in a timely manner, it’s crucial that the window is marked as needing display and that the display will occur soon (that is, within the next second). When you invoke "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "disableScreenUpdatesUntilFlush"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ", you can make sure that a marked window gets displayed by returning control to the run loop on the main thread or by sending the window "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/appkit/nswindow/1419096-displayifneeded"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " or "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/appkit/nswindow/1419358-display"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ". If it’s unclear whether the window is marked as needing display, you can also ensure that a display occurs by using "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/appkit/nsview/1483475-setneedsdisplayinrect"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " for a view that’s visible in the window."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  ],
